<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Van Breda Kolff To Get Pepperdine Job </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MALIBU, Calif. (AP) -- Jan van Breda Kolff, recently fired after  
six years at Vanderbilt, was expected to be introduced tomorrow as 
the new men's basketball coach at Pepperdine. 
</P>
<P>
	A news conference was scheduled for 11 a.m. PDT in Heritage Hall  
on campus. 
</P>
<P>
	Van Breda Kolff will succeed Lorenzo Romar, who resigned March  
26 to accept the head coaching job at Saint Louis. 
</P>
<P>
	``... I have every reason to believe that Jan can continue to  
move our program forward,'' Pepperdine athletic director John 
Watson said. 
</P>
<P>
	Van Breda Kolff had a 104-81 record in six seasons at  
Vanderbilt, which advanced to postseason play four times, including 
a first-round loss in the 1997 NCAA tournament. The Commodores were 
14-15 this season. 
</P>
<P>
	Van Breda Kolff, 47, is the son of former NBA coach Butch van  
Breda Kolff. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
