<HEADLINE> Daughter Seeks To Honor Jim Thorpe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PRAGUE, Okla. (AP) -- Jim Thorpe's 77-year-old daughter is  
orchestrating a drive to get her father declared the 20th century's 
top athlete. 
</P>
<P>
	Grace Thorpe hopes to collect enough signatures on a petition to  
convince sportswriters and broadcasters that her father was the 
best athlete of the 1900s. 
</P>
<P>
	Thorpe was the 1912 Olympic track champion and also played pro  
football and baseball. Thorpe is the only person to have won gold 
medals in both the Olympic pentathlon and decathlon. 
</P>
<P>
	``Dad was not only good at one sport. He was good at three,''  
Ms. Thorpe said. ``There's no competition.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The ``Athlete of the Century'' petition drive she instigated  
about four years ago so far has yielded about 4,000 signatures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
