<HEADLINE> Sunday's NFL Draft Selections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Selections Sunday from the 1999 NFL draft with  
team, player, projected position and college (x-supplemental 
selection; y-compensatory selection): 
</P>
<P>
                           *Fourth Round    	
</P>
<P>
	96. Indianapolis (from Cleveland through San Francisco), Paul  
Miranda, db, Central Florida. 
</P>
<P>
	97. Cincinnati, John Welbourn, ot, California.  
</P>
<P>
	98. Philadelphia, Craig Yeast, wr, Kentucky.  
</P>
<P>
	99. San Francisco (from Indianapolis), Anthony Parker, db, Weber  
State. 
</P>
<P>
	100. Carolina, Hannial Navies, lb, Colorado.  
</P>
<P>
	101. St. Louis, Joe Germaine, qb, Ohio State.  
</P>
<P>
	102. Oakland (from Chicago), Dameane Douglas, wr, California.  
