<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bosox Put Reliever Tom Gordon on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Relief ace Tom Gordon was put on the 15-day  
disabled list by the Boston Red Sox on Sunday because of a strained 
right elbow. 
</P>
<P>
	Gordon missed the first two weeks of spring training with the  
same injury. He reaggravated it Saturday in the ninth inning after 
throwing five pitches against the Tampa Bay Devil Rays. 
</P>
<P>
	Red Sox officials said Gordon was sent Sunday to the University  
of Massachusetts Medical Center in Worcester for an MRI. 
</P>
<P>
	Boston manager Jimy Williams would not discuss who will take  
Gordon's spot as his closer. 
</P>
<P>
	``Flash is still our closer,'' Williams said. ``We will not  
designate anyone for that role until we need to.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Boston is expected to use Derek Lowe, Mark Guthrie, Kip Gross  
and Jim Corsi to finish games until Gordon returns. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think we have several pitchers out there that can close a  
game,'' Williams said. ``I don't think there is any one particular 
individual that I'm going to go to and say, `Hey, you are our 
closer.' '' 
</P>
<P>
	Gordon set a major league record for consecutive saves last  
season with 43 finishing with a league-leading 46, a team record. 
He has converted three of five save chances this year, striking out 
eight in 3 2-3 scoreless innings. 
</P>
<P>
	Boston recalled right-hander Brian Rose from Triple-A Pawtucket  
to take Gordon's spot on the roster. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
