<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Players Ejected in Baseball Brawl </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Three players were ejected following a  
bench-clearing brawl in tonight's game between the Seattle Mariners 
and Anaheim Angels. 
</P>
<P>
	Anaheim's Todd Greene charged the mound after being hit in the  
fourth inning by Seattle rookie Brett Hinchliffe, who had just 
given up a homer to Troy Glaus that cut the Mariners' lead to 5-3. 
</P>
<P>
	Greene and Hinchcliffe exchanged punches and were both ejected  
along with Angels pitcher Tim Belcher following the five-minute 
skirmish. John Halama replaced Hinchliffe, who was making his first 
major league start. 
</P>
<P>
	Tensions started the previous inning, when Ken Griffey Jr. was  
hit by Anaheim pitcher Steve Sparks three batters after Domingo 
Cedeno homered for the Mariners. Before trotting to first base, 
Griffey pointed with his bat toward the Angels dugout. 
</P>
<P>
	On Friday night, Glaus was hit by a pitch from Jamie Moyer to  
load the bases, and Greene hit the next pitch for a grand slam to 
seal Anaheim's 9-5 victory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
