<HEADLINE> Nash Donates Works to Getty Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Graham Nash has donated two works by American  
photographer Edward Steichen to the J. Paul Getty Museum. 
</P>
<P>
	Nash, one-third of Crosby, Stills and Nash, gave the museum a  
1904 photo called ``Wedding Self-Portrait,'' one of only three 
known prints from the negative, and an untitled 1930 picture of 
Steichen's grandchildren, the museum announced Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Nash and his wife, Susan, are photography enthusiasts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
