<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Charismatic Solidifies Derby Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- Charismatic blew by Yankee Victor in the  
final furlong and solidified a Kentucky Derby trip by winning 
today's $378,000 Coolmore Lexington Stakes at Keeneland. 
</P>
<P>
	Charismatic was third behind Yankee Victor and pacesetter Texas  
Glitter around the second turn. As Texas Glitter faded in the final 
quarter-mile, Charismatic surged past Yankee Victor on the outside, 
drawing away for a 2 1/2-length victory in the last major Kentucky 
Derby prep race. 
</P>
<P>
	Charismatic, a 12-1 shot, ran the 1 1-16 miles in a  
stakes-record 1:41.06, paying $26.20, $10.20 and $6.20. Yankee 
Victor paid $6.40 and $4, while Finder's Gold, trained by Bob 
Baffert, was three-quarters of a length farther back and paid 
$4.80. 
</P>
<P>
	Texas Glitter, the favorite in a 12-horse field, finished tenth,  
more than 20 lengths off the pace. 
</P>
<P>
	Trainer D. Wayne Lukas said he told Charismatic's owners, Bob  
and Beverly Lewis, Saturday that he wanted to run the colt in the 
May 1 Kentucky Derby regardless of whether he won or lost on 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	``It wouldn't have mattered how he ran,'' Lukas said, adding  
that he thought Charismatic had the earnings needed to get into the 
expected 20-horse Derby field even before his $235,000 Lexington 
Stakes payday. 
</P>
<P>
	Jockey Jerry Bailey followed Lukas' instructions to keep  
Charismatic a little closer to the lead pack than he normally 
might, moving him to fourth by the half-mile, third at the 
three-quarters and into second behind Yankee Victor at the top of 
the stretch. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was a textbook ride,'' Lukas said. ``It just unfolded  
right.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Charismatic is expected to need a new mount for the Derby, as  
Bailey has committed to ride Worldly Manner for the Maktoum family 
of the United Arab Emirates at Churchill Downs. 
</P>
<P>
	Bailey rushed off to make a flight to New York and was not  
available for comment, but Lukas said the jockey made a tantalizing 
remark as he left. 
</P>
<P>
	``He said, `Don't do anything until you talk to me,''' Lukas  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Lukas said he has spoken to Laffit Pincay Jr. about riding  
Charismatic. However, Pincay, who is chasing Bill Shoemaker's 
career wins record, is slated to ride several favorites at 
Hollywood Park on May 1. 
</P>
<P>
	Finding a jockey for Charismatic after Sunday's performance  
shouldn't be too hard, the trainer said. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think the phone will start ringing,'' he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
