<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> O's 1B Will Clark Breaks Left Thumb </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Baltimore Orioles first baseman Will Clark  
fractured his left thumb in Sunday's game against the Toronto Blue 
Jays, another blow to the struggling team. 
</P>
<P>
	Clark attempted to field Willie Greene's one-hopper in the first  
inning but the ball skipped off his thumb and bounced to second 
baseman Delino Deshields, who threw to Clark for the third out. 
</P>
<P>
	Clark was taken to a hospital, where X-rays revealed the break.  
While the team traveled to Tampa after the game, Clark returned to 
Baltimore. 
</P>
<P>
	Cal Ripken missed his fourth game of the season on Sunday with  
severe back pain. He headed to Cleveland for a Monday exam. 
</P>
