<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Boston Marathon Forecast Looks OK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- The 103rd Boston Marathon should get off to a  
sunny start, with clouds increasing throughout the day and the 
chance of a shower later in the afternoon, forecasters said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Sun in the morning Monday should stick around for the race's  
noon start, but clouds will roll in over the following few hours, 
according to the National Weather Service. 
</P>
<P>
	The temperature at start time should be around 55 degrees, with  
highs of around 60 degrees by mid-afternoon. There is a 30 percent 
chance of a shower, which meteorologists said would hit the area 
after 3 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
	Forecasters said the air will be moderately dry, with humidity  
between 40 and 60 percent, and winds will be out of the southwest 
with speeds of five to 15 mph as the race gets under way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
