<DOCNO> APW19990418.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-18 15:10:48 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Calif. Federal Bank To Appeal Fine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- California Federal Bank will appeal a $23.3  
million award to the savings and loan, calling the judgment 
``flawed.'' The bank originally had sought more than $1.5 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	``The $23.3 million award falls far short of CalFed's actual  
damages,'' spokesman Walter G. Montgomery said Sunday in a 
statement. 
</P>
<P>
	Judge Robert H. Hodges Jr. of the U.S. Court of Federal Claims  
on Friday found the government breached its contract with CalFed. 
</P>
<P>
	The case stems from a 1996 Supreme Court decision that said the  
government broke its contract with thrift institutions when it 
changed the rules on how they must count their assets as part of an 
S&AMP;L bailout in 1989. 
</P>
<P>
	CalFed said last week's decision is ``flawed'' and agrees  
``neither with applicable law nor with the extensive evidence and 
testimony presented at trial.'' 
</P>
<P>
	San Francisco-based Golden State Bancorp is the publicly traded  
parent company of CalFed. 


</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990418.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-18 17:12:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bonds Misses Giants' Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- Barry Bonds was scratched from the San Francisco  
Giants' starting lineup today because of a sore left elbow, and 
will have an MRI performed on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's had a little tenderness and little soreness,'' Giants  
manager Dusty Baker said before a 12-3 loss to Arizona. 
</P>
<P>
	The left fielder, who is tied for third in the NL lead with 12  
RBIs, was examined during the Giants' game against the Arizona 
Diamondbacks. 
</P>
<P>
	He will be checked again when the Giants return to San Francisco  
on Monday. Baker said Bonds' availability for Monday night's game 
against the Florida Marlins depends on the result of the MRI. 
</P>
<P>
	Bonds, an eight-time All-Star with the Giants and Pittsburgh  
Pirates, is hitting .366 with four home runs. He was replaced in 
the lineup by Stan Javier, who went 1-for-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
